vim-mysql: Vim mysql made simple.

Put cursor on SQL paragraph and :Mysql 
Output in myfile.txt by default or in specified file, 'test.txt' in sample bellow. 
Open output from another vim instance with autoread to see it instantly.

Sample.mysql
-----------------------------------------
# Sample.mysql
mySQLcmd:     ssh user@gc-db1 "mysql -u test -ppasswd dbname"
defaultFile:  myfile.txt

# check xyz in test
test.txt:
   Select * from test
   where a = 'xyz'
   limit 10

# show all test tables
show tables like '%test%'

show create table testÂ¥G  
              
-----------------------------------------

